#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:41
msgid "Setting up a Git Server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:44
msgid ""
"The following instructions will install a <application>git</application> "
"server. It will be set up to use <application>OpenSSH</application> as the "
"secure remote access method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:51
msgid "Configuration of the server consists of the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:55
msgid "1. Setup Users, Groups, and Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:58
msgid ""
"You will need to be user <systemitem class='username'>root</systemitem> for "
"the initial portion of configuration. Create the <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">git</systemitem> user and group with the following "
"commands:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:64
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>groupadd -g &gitgid; git &amp;&amp;\n"
"useradd -c \"git Owner\" -d /home/git -m -g git -s /usr/bin/git-shell -u &gituid; git</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>groupadd -g &gitgid; git &amp;&amp;\n"
"useradd -c \"git Owner\" -d /home/git -m -g git -s /usr/bin/git-shell -u &gituid; git</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:68
msgid ""
"Create some files and directories in the home directory of the git user "
"allowing access to the git repository using ssh keys."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>install -o git -g git -dm0700 /home/git/.ssh &amp;&amp;\n"
"install -o git -g git -m0600 /dev/null /home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys\n"
"</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>install -o git -g git -dm0700 /home/git/.ssh &amp;&amp;\n"
"install -o git -g git -m0600 /dev/null /home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys\n"
"</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:77
msgid ""
"For any developer who should have access to the repository add his/her "
"public ssh key to <filename>/home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys</filename>.  "
"First, prepend some options to prevent users from using the connection to "
"git for port forwarding to other machines the git server might reach."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:84
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>echo -n \"no-port-forwarding,no-X11-forwarding,no-agent-forwarding,no-pty \" >> /home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys &amp;&amp;\n"
"cat &lt;user-ssh-key&gt; &gt;&gt; /home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>echo -n \"no-port-forwarding,no-X11-forwarding,no-agent-forwarding,no-pty \" >> /home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys &amp;&amp;\n"
"cat &lt;user-ssh-key&gt; &gt;&gt; /home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:88
msgid ""
"It is also useful to set the default name of the initial branch of new "
"repositories by modifying the git configuration. As the <systemitem "
"class='username'>root</systemitem> user, run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>git config --global init.defaultBranch trunk</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>git config --global init.defaultBranch trunk</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:96
msgid ""
"Finally add the <filename>/usr/bin/git-shell</filename> entry to the "
"<filename>/etc/shells</filename> configuration file. This shell has been set"
" in the <systemitem class='username'>git</systemitem> user profile and is to"
" make sure that only git related actions can be executed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>echo \"/usr/bin/git-shell\" &gt;&gt; /etc/shells</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>echo \"/usr/bin/git-shell\" &gt;&gt; /etc/shells</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:108
msgid "2. Create a git repository"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:111
msgid ""
"The repository can be anywhere on the filesystem. It is important that the "
"git user has read/write access to that location. We use <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/srv/git</filename> as base directory. Create a new "
"<application>git</application> repository with the following commands (as "
"the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><note><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:121
msgid ""
"In all the instructions below, we use <emphasis>project1</emphasis> as an "
"example repository name.  You should name your repository as a short "
"descriptive name for your specific project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>install -o git -g git -m755 -d /srv/git/project1.git &amp;&amp;\n"
"cd /srv/git/project1.git                             &amp;&amp;\n"
"git init --bare                                      &amp;&amp;\n"
"chown -R git:git .</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>install -o git -g git -m755 -d /srv/git/project1.git &amp;&amp;\n"
"cd /srv/git/project1.git                             &amp;&amp;\n"
"git init --bare                                      &amp;&amp;\n"
"chown -R git:git .</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:135
msgid "3. Populate the repository from a client system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><note><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:139
msgid ""
"All the instructions in this section and the next should be done on a user "
"system, not the server system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:145
msgid ""
"Now that the repository is created, it can be used by the developers to put "
"some files into it. Once the ssh key of the user is imported to git's "
"<filename>authorized_keys</filename> file, the user can interact with the "
"repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:152
msgid ""
"A minimal configuration should be available on the developer's system "
"specifying its user name and the email address.  Create this minimal config "
"file on client side:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:157
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.gitconfig &lt;&lt;EOF\n"
"[user]\n"
"\tname = &lt;users-name&gt;\n"
"\temail = &lt;users-email-address&gt;\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.gitconfig &lt;&lt;EOF\n"
"[user]\n"
"\tname = &lt;users-name&gt;\n"
"\temail = &lt;users-email-address&gt;\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:164
msgid ""
"On the developer's machine, setup some files to be pushed to the repository "
"as the initial content:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><note><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:170
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>gitserver</emphasis> term used below should be the host name "
"(or ip address) of the git server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir myproject\n"
"cd myproject\n"
"git init --initial-branch=trunk\n"
"git remote add origin git@gitserver:/srv/git/project1.git\n"
"cat &gt;README &lt;&lt;EOF\n"
"This is the README file\n"
"EOF\n"
"git add README\n"
"git commit -m 'Initial creation of README'\n"
"git push --set-upstream origin trunk</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mkdir myproject\n"
"cd myproject\n"
"git init --initial-branch=trunk\n"
"git remote add origin git@gitserver:/srv/git/project1.git\n"
"cat &gt;README &lt;&lt;EOF\n"
"This is the README file\n"
"EOF\n"
"git add README\n"
"git commit -m 'Initial creation of README'\n"
"git push --set-upstream origin trunk</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:186
msgid ""
"The initial content is now pushed to the server and is available for other "
"users. On the current machine, the argument <literal>--set-upstream origin "
"trunk</literal> is now no longer required as the local repository is now "
"connected to the remote repository. Subsequent pushes can be performed as"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>git push</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>git push</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:197
msgid ""
"Other developers can now clone the repository and do modifications to the "
"content (as long as their ssh keys has been installed):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:202
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>git clone git@gitserver:/srv/git/project1.git\n"
"cd project1\n"
"vi README\n"
"git commit -am 'Fix for README file'\n"
"git push</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>git clone git@gitserver:/srv/git/project1.git\n"
"cd project1\n"
"vi README\n"
"git commit -am 'Fix for README file'\n"
"git push</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><note><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:210
msgid ""
"This is a very basic server setup based on "
"<application>OpenSSH</application> access. All developers are using the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">git</systemitem> user to perform actions on "
"the repository and the changes users are commiting can be distiguished as "
"the local user name (see <filename>~/.gitconfig</filename>) is recorded in "
"the changesets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:220
msgid ""
"Access is restricted by the public keys added to git's "
"<filename>authorized_keys</filename> file and there is no option for the "
"public to export/clone the repository. To enable this, continue with step 4 "
"to set up the git server for public read-only access."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:230
msgid "4. Configure the Server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:233
msgid ""
"The setup described above makes a repository available for authenticated "
"users (via providing the ssh public key file).  There is also a simple way "
"to publish the repository to unauthenticated users &mdash; of course without"
" write access."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:241
msgid ""
"The combination of access via ssh (for authenticated users) and the export "
"of repositories to unauthenticated users via the daemon is in most cases "
"enough for a development site."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><note><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:248
msgid ""
"The daemon will be reachable at port <literal>9418</literal> by default. "
"Make sure that your firewall setup allows access to that port."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:255
msgid ""
"To start the server at boot time, install the git-daemon bootscript included"
" in the <xref linkend=\"bootscripts\"/> package:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><indexterm><primary>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:260
msgid "git"
msgstr "git"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:263
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:275
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>make install-git-daemon</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>make install-git-daemon</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:266
msgid ""
"To start the server at boot time, install the <filename>git-"
"daemon.service</filename> unit from the <xref linkend=\"systemd-units\"/> "
"package:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><indexterm><primary>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:272
msgid "gitserve"
msgstr "gitserve"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:278
msgid ""
"In order to allow <application>git</application> to export a repository, a "
"file named <filename>git-daemon-export-ok</filename> is required in each "
"repository directory on the server. The file needs no content, just its "
"existance enables, its absence disables the export of that repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:285
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>touch /srv/git/project1.git/git-daemon-export-ok</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>touch /srv/git/project1.git/git-daemon-export-ok</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:288
msgid ""
"The script to start the git daemon uses some default values internally. Most"
" important is the path to the repository directory which is set to <filename"
" class=\"directory\">/srv/git</filename>.  In case you have for whatever "
"reason created the repository in a different location, you'll need to tell "
"the boot script where the repository is to be found. This can be achieved by"
" creating a configuration file named <filename>/etc/sysconfig/git-"
"daemon</filename>.  This configuration file will be imported if it exists. "
"It can look like:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:298
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Begin /etc/sysconfig/git-daemon\n"
"\n"
"# Specify the location of the git repository\n"
"GIT_BASE_DIR=\"/srv/git/\"\n"
"\n"
"# Directories added to whitelist\n"
"DFT_REPO_DIR=\"$GIT_BASE_DIR\"\n"
"\n"
"# Add extra options which will appended to the 'git daemon'\n"
"# command executed in the boot script\n"
"GIT_DAEMON_OPTS=\"\"\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/sysconfig/git-daemon\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:313
msgid ""
"Along with the <filename>git-daemon.service</filename> unit, a configuration"
" file named <filename>/etc/default/git-daemon</filename> has been installed."
" Review this configuration file to match your needs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:320
msgid "There are only three options to set in the configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:324
msgid "GIT_BASE_DIR=&lt;dirname&gt;"
msgstr "GIT_BASE_DIR=&lt;dirname&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:326
msgid ""
"Specify the location of the repository directory on which the git daemon "
"operates on. Relative pathes in access to the daemon will translated to be "
"relative to this directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:334
msgid "DFT_REPO_DIR=&lt;dirname&gt;"
msgstr "DFT_REPO_DIR=&lt;dirname&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:336
msgid ""
"The directory is added to the white list of allowed directories. This "
"variable can hold multible directory names but is usually set equal to "
"<literal>GIT_BASE_DIR</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:343
msgid "GIT_DAEMON_OPTS=&lt;options&gt;"
msgstr "GIT_DAEMON_OPTS=&lt;options&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/general/prog/gitserver.xml:345
msgid ""
"In case you have to pass special options to the <command>git "
"daemon</command> command, they have to be specified in this setting. One "
"example might be to adjust the port number where daemon is listening. In "
"this case, add <literal>--port=&lt;port number&gt;</literal> to this "
"variable.  For more information about which options can be set, take a look "
"at the output of <command>git daemon --help</command>."
msgstr ""

